      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SEGER (8) hit the ground running with a slick early sectional but ran over late and missed the frame when a 2.25 lengths fourth (38.41) over 660m at Bendigo. Has claims if he runs up to expectations. SOCIALISM (2) missed the frame and was safely held latest finishing 6th at Ballarat following on from a third place finish (30.75) at this track the start prior. Should be about the money. GLOWING ETHICS (4) has been mixing form lately, hitting the frame two back before finishing sixth (35.26) at Sandown in a Grade 5. Expecting significant improvement this line-up. TO PERU (5) won by a wide margin last start. Hard to beat again.",
